cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating and reconstructing 3D objects from 2D images and range scans. It may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves creating and manipulating 3D shapes. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the mention of the Wasserstein distance and gradient penalization suggests that it could also be classified under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
